**Q. (b)** Write a C program to implement the **Josephus problem** using a circular linked list for `n = 7` people and `k = 3` (every 3rd person is eliminated). Show the elimination order and identify the survivor. **(7 marks)**

**Model Solution:** (Refer to Section 3.5 Algorithm E)

**Dry-run for n=7, k=3:**

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Initial ring:} \quad & 1 \rightarrow 2 \rightarrow 3 \rightarrow 4 \rightarrow 5 \rightarrow 6 \rightarrow 7 \rightarrow 1 \\
\text{Count 1, 2, 3:} \quad & \text{Eliminate } 3 \\
\text{Remaining:} \quad & 1 \rightarrow 2 \rightarrow 4 \rightarrow 5 \rightarrow 6 \rightarrow 7 \rightarrow 1 \\
\text{Count 1, 2, 3 from 4:} \quad & \text{Eliminate } 6 \\
\text{Remaining:} \quad & 1 \rightarrow 2 \rightarrow 4 \rightarrow 5 \rightarrow 7 \rightarrow 1 \\
\text{Count 1, 2, 3 from 7:} \quad & \text{Eliminate } 2 \\
\text{Remaining:} \quad & 1 \rightarrow 4 \rightarrow 5 \rightarrow 7 \rightarrow 1 \\
\text{Count 1, 2, 3 from 4:} \quad & \text{Eliminate } 7 \\
\text{Remaining:} \quad & 1 \rightarrow 4 \rightarrow 5 \rightarrow 1 \\
\text{Count 1, 2, 3 from 1:} \quad & \text{Eliminate } 5 \\
\text{Remaining:} \quad & 1 \rightarrow 4 \rightarrow 1 \\
\text{Count 1, 2, 3 from 4:} \quad & \text{Eliminate } 1 \\
\text{Survivor:} \quad & \boxed{4}
\end{aligned}
$$

**Elimination order:** 3 → 6 → 2 → 7 → 5 → 1 → **Survivor: 4**

**Verification with closed-form formula:**

$$
\begin{aligned}
J(1, 3) &= 0 \\
J(2, 3) &= (0 + 3) \bmod 2 = 1 \\
J(3, 3) &= (1 + 3) \bmod 3 = 1 \\
J(4, 3) &= (1 + 3) \bmod 4 = 0 \\
J(5, 3) &= (0 + 3) \bmod 5 = 3 \\
J(6, 3) &= (3 + 3) \bmod 6 = 0 \\
J(7, 3) &= (0 + 3) \bmod 7 = 3 \\
\text{Result } = J(7, 3) + 1 &= 4 \quad \checkmark
\end{aligned}
$$

